{"parse":{"title":"Nose tomb","pageid":16663596,"revid":838603449,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:202px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:WakouLandingColor.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6d/WakouLandingColor.jpg/200px-WakouLandingColor.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"304\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6d/WakouLandingColor.jpg/300px-WakouLandingColor.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6d/WakouLandingColor.jpg/400px-WakouLandingColor.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"414\" data-file-height=\"630\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:WakouLandingColor.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Japanese invasion of Korea in 1592</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Nose tombs</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Japanese_language\" title=\"Japanese language\">Japanese</a>: <span lang=\"ja\">\u9f3b\u306e\u5893</span> <i>hana no haka</i>; <a href=\"/wiki/Korean_language\" title=\"Korean language\">Korean</a>: <span lang=\"ko\">\ucf54 \ubb34\ub364</span> <i>ko mudeom</i>) are <a href=\"/wiki/Tombs\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tombs\">tombs</a> that contain <a href=\"/wiki/Human_nose\" title=\"Human nose\">human noses</a> or other body parts that were brought back to <a href=\"/wiki/Japan\" title=\"Japan\">Japan</a> as trophies during the <a href=\"/wiki/Japanese_invasions_of_Korea_(1592%E2%80%931598)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Japanese invasions of Korea (1592\u20131598)\">Japanese invasions of Korea</a> in the late 16th century.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/wiki/War_trophies\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"War trophies\">War trophies</a> were a part of Japanese tradition at the time and <a href=\"/wiki/Samurai\" title=\"Samurai\">samurai</a> warriors were often paid according to how many they collected.\n</p><p>One such nose tomb was discovered in 1983 in <a href=\"/wiki/Okayama\" title=\"Okayama\">Okayama</a> near <a href=\"/wiki/Osaka\" title=\"Osaka\">Osaka</a>. This tomb held the <a href=\"/wiki/Rhinotomy\" title=\"Rhinotomy\">severed</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Pickled\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pickled\">pickled</a> noses of approximately 20,000 dead Koreans which were eventually returned to Korea in 1992 and cremated.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> A similar tomb still exists today in <a href=\"/wiki/Kyoto\" title=\"Kyoto\">Kyoto</a> called the <a href=\"/wiki/Mimizuka\" title=\"Mimizuka\">Mimizuka</a>, literally \"Ear Mound\", although it contains noses and not ears.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In Japan, these tombs are considered relics by the few who are aware of them, but in Korea these tombs are very well known.<sup id=\"cite_ref-kristof_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-kristof-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Nose_tomb&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Japan-Korea_relations\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Japan-Korea relations\">Japan-Korea relations</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Human_trophy_collecting\" title=\"Human trophy collecting\">Human trophy collecting</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Nose_tomb&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Diamond, Jared (2004-10-27). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.asianresearch.org/articles/2348.html\">\"The Japanese Roots (Part 1)\"</a>. Association for Asia Research<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2010-10-26</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=The+Japanese+Roots+%28Part+1%29&amp;rft.pub=Association+for+Asia+Research&amp;rft.date=2004-10-27&amp;rft.aulast=Diamond&amp;rft.aufirst=Jared&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.asianresearch.org%2Farticles%2F2348.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANose+tomb\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/1992-09-23/news/9209231027_1_noses-lopped-koreans\">\"20,000 Noses Of Koreans Being Returned By Japan\"</a>. Orlando Sentinel. September 23, 1992<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">6 December</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=20%2C000+Noses+Of+Koreans+Being+Returned+By+Japan&amp;rft.pub=Orlando+Sentinel&amp;rft.date=1992-09-23&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Farticles.orlandosentinel.com%2F1992-09-23%2Fnews%2F9209231027_1_noses-lopped-koreans&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANose+tomb\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"disp